<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="alate viviparous female">
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Alate viviparous female</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="8">(Fig. 4C). Head brown, as dark as thorax. Abdominal segments 1 and 2 with spinal sclerites; segments 4-5 with spinopleural patch, sometimes partially joined with the spinopleural bands on 3 and 6; segments 1-6 with marginal sclerites; segment 7 with a band paler than previously mentioned sclerites; segment 8 with pale setiferous sclerites, sometimes coalesced together. Metric and meristic features in Table 3.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
